%% The two load-bearing cross-node contracts: spec/blueprint.json + window.__GAME__
%% W1 DRAFTS assertions over the hook → VERIFY-1 HARDENS the design into a FROZEN blueprint
%% (Given/When/Then acceptanceCriteria + referenceSolution + declaredRanges) → W2 finalizes +
%% exposes the accessor → W4 POPULATES it from REAL state → VERIFY-2 READS it to assert FIDELITY
%% (and perturbs within declaredRanges). Both oracles — gdd.json AND blueprint.json — are immutable.
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant W1 as W1 · Spec (Designer)
  participant V1 as VERIFY-1 · Design (Critic)
  participant BP as spec/blueprint.json (FROZEN oracle)
  participant W2 as W2 · Scaffold (Coder)
  participant H as window.__GAME__ hook
  participant W4 as W4 · Execute (Executor)
  participant V2 as VERIFY-2 · QA (Playtester)

  Note over W1,V2: The filesystem is the contract — nodes hand off ONLY via on-disk artifacts

  W1->>H: DRAFT assertions over the hook (observe player.y / score / status …)
  Note right of W1: writes spec/gdd.json — the design THESIS (immutable provenance)

  W1->>V1: spec/gdd.json + spec/PLAN.md
  V1->>BP: HARDEN + FREEZE — complete config · concrete layout (coords/routes/timings)
  Note right of V1: rubric + kinematic feasibility math + threat-on-reward-path
  V1->>BP: author referenceSolution (proof it is winnable) + Given/When/Then acceptanceCriteria + declaredRanges
  Note right of V1: blueprint.json is now the SINGLE source of truth for W2/W3/W4/VERIFY-2

  V1->>H: UPGRADE W1's drafts → acceptanceCriteria over the hook
  W2->>H: FINALIZE canonical accessor (superset) and template EXPOSES it
  Note right of W2: template-contract.md §3: ready/status/scene/player/score/entities + snapshot()

  W4->>BP: read layout/config/coupling/referenceSolution VERBATIM (zero design latitude)
  W4->>H: POPULATE from REAL state (score via registry · status at the real win/lose/respawn point)
  Note right of W4: anti-contortion — NEVER fake __GAME__, tune to the driver radius, or disable a threat

  V2->>BP: read acceptanceCriteria · referenceSolution · declaredRanges
  V2->>H: READ to assert FIDELITY (Given/When/Then from KNOWN preconditions)
  H-->>V2: live values
  V2->>H: ISOMORPHIC PERTURBATION — re-run permuted WITHIN declaredRanges

  alt build is a FAITHFUL, invariant realization
    V2->>V2: emit VALIDATION_PASSED
  else implementation bug (build ≠ blueprint / diverges under perturbation)
    V2->>W4: bounded ≤3 self-fix — edit src/** GAME CODE only
    Note over W4,V2: NEVER edit gdd / blueprint / referenceSolution / hook / harness — the oracle stays immutable
  else genuine DESIGN problem (blueprint unwinnable even when built faithfully)
    V2->>V1: escalate — write escalations.M<id>.json (routes to VERIFY-1, NOT the executor)
  end
